description: The chloroplast-containing, photosynthetic parenchymatous tissue situated between the two epidermal layers of the leaf or leaf like organs.

label: pith
description: A maximal portion of parenchyma [PO:0005421] in the center of a shoot axis [PO:0025029] or root [PO:0009005].

label: spongy mesophyll cell
description: Irregularly-shaped, chlorenchymatous cell, separated by large air spaces.

label: palisade mesophyll cell
description: Elongated chlorenchymatous cell oriented perpendicular to the leaf surface and which is active in photosynthesis.

label: juvenile vascular leaf
description: A vascular leaf that is distinct from adult leaves, being characterized by particular anatomical traits namely, wax and trichome distribution, presence or absence of epidermal cell types, cell wall shape and biochemistry.

label: adult vascular leaf
description: A vascular leaf characterized by particular anatomical traits namely, wax and trichome distribution, presence or absence of epidermal cell types, cell wall shape and biochemistry.

label: leaf trichome
description: A phyllome trichome that is part of a leaf epidermis.

label: whole plant flowering stage
description: A sporophyte reproductive stage [PO:0007130] during which a flower [PO:0009046] on a whole plant [PO:0000003] is open.

label: seed germination stage
description: A sporophyte vegetative stage [PO:0007134] which begins with the onset of a seed imbibition stage [PO:0007022] and ends with a radicle emergence stage [PO: 0007015], or a coleorhiza emergence stage [PO:0025475], as a result of the growth by the plant embryo [PO:0004537] in a seed [PO:0009010].

label: LP.01 one leaf visible stage
description: The stage at which leaves at one node, other than the cotyledonary node, are visible above ground. In the taxa with hypogeal type germination the first leaf on the epicotyl is leaf 1, and in grasses, the coleoptile is leaf 1. The leaves can be a single leaf, two, or whorls of leaves at each node.

label: fruit distal end
description: A cardinal part of multi-tissue plant structure (PO:0025498) that is the end of a fruit (PO:0009001) distal from a fruit pedicel (PO:0004536).

label: fruit proximal end
description: A cardinal part of multi-tissue plant structure (PO:0025498) that is the end of a fruit (PO:0009001) proximal to a fruit pedicel (PO:0004536).

label: tertiary leaf vein
description: A leaf lamina vein (PO:0020138) arising from a secondary leaf vein (PO:0020140). Vein orders only apply to hierarchically branching vein patterns, not to dichotomously branching vein patterns, as found in some ferns and gymnosperms.

label: stomata; stomatal pore
description: A plant anatomical space that forms an opening in an epidermis, flanked by two guard cells.

label: fruit
description: A multi-tissue plant structure [PO:0025496] that develops from a gynoecium [PO:0009062], or a single carpel [PO:0009030], and at maturity may have as parts one or more seeds [PO:0009010].

label: root
description: A plant axis [PO:0025004] that lacks shoot axis nodes [PO:0005004] and usually grows indeterminately.

label: shoot system
description: A collective plant organ structure (PO:0025007) that produces shoot-borne portions of meristem tissue (PO:0009013) and the plant structures (PO:0009011) that arise from them.

label: portion of plant tissue
description: A plant structure [PO:0009011] that consists predominantly of similarly specialized plant cells [PO:0009002] of one or more types.

label: plant organ
description: A multi-tissue plant structure (PO:0025496) that is a functional unit, is a proper part of a whole plant (PO:0000003), and includes portions of plant tissue (PO:0009007) of at least two different types that derive from a common developmental path.

label: plant embryo
description: A whole plant [PO:0000003] that participates in the plant embryo stage [PO:0007631].

label: seed
description: A multi-tissue plant structure [PO:0025496] that develops from a plant ovule [PO:0020003] and has as parts a plant embryo [PO:0009009] enclosed in a seed coat [PO:0009088].

label: plant structure
description: A plant anatomical entity [PO:0025131] that is, or was, part of a plant, or was derived from a part of a plant.

label: leaf axil
description: An axil that is the space between a shoot axis and a leaf that branches from the shoot axis.

label: stamen
description: A microsporophyll bearing one or more microsporangia.

label: carpel
description: A megasporophyll, almost always at the center of a flower, its margins more or less fused together or with other carpels to enclose the ovule(s).

label: sepal
description: A phyllome [PO:0006001] that is usually green, and is part of the calyx [PO:0009060]. In some species the sepals [PO:0009031] may not be green for example many members of the Liliaceae family.

label: petal
description: A phyllome [PO:0006001] that is part of the corolla [PO:0009059], and is usually colored [not green]. In some species the petal [PO:0009032] may not be colored.

label: tepal
description: There is no differentiation between the petals [PO:0009032] and the sepals [PO:0009031] in color, placement, and size [e.g. some species of Magnolia]. A phyllome [PO:0006001] that is part of a perianth [PO:0009058] where it is not possible to distinguish between the petals [PO:0009032] and sepals [PO:0009031].

label: flower
description: A determinate reproductive shoot system [PO:0025082] that has as part at least one carpel [PO:0009030] or at least one stamen [PO:0009029] and does not contain any other determinate shoot system [PO:0009006] as a part.

label: stem
description: A shoot axis [PO:0025029] that is the primary axis of a plant.

label: perianth
description: The perianth can consist of only the corolla [PO:0009059], only the calyx [PO:0009060] or it may have both structures in a complete flower. If the petals [PO:0009032] and sepals [PO:0009031] are indistinguishable from one another, the perianth consists of just a collective tepal structure [PO:0025021], composed of one or more tepals [PO:0009033], for example in tulip or lily flowers. A collective phyllome structure [PO:0025023] that includes as parts the corolla [PO:0009059] and/or the calyx [PO:0009060]; or one or more tepals [PO:0009033].

label: corolla
description: A collective phyllome structure (PO:0025023) that is composed of one or more petals (PO:0009032), comprising the inner whorl of non-reproductive floral organs (PO:0025395) and surrounds the androecium (PO:0009061) and the gynoecium (PO:0009062).

label: calyx
description: A collective phyllome structure [PO:0025023] that is composed of one or more sepals [PO:0009031], and comprises the outer whorl of non-reproductive floral organs [PO:0025395]. The calyx is part of the perianth [PO:0009058]. This definition is based on the perfect flower, which has all four whorls. In many species, and in mutants one or more of the whorls are missing.

label: androecium
description: A collective phyllome structure [PO:0025023] composed all of the stamens [PO:0009029] in a flower [PO:0009046]. The androecium also has as parts any staminodes [PO:0009077] that may be present in a flower. If annotating gene expression to an androecium with a single stamen [PO:0009029], the annotation should go on stamen. If you are annotating to this structure for Zea mays, please also add an annotation to the corresponding floret type. Choose the most specific term possible from: spikelet floret [PO:0009082], ear floret [PO:0006354], lower floret of pedicellate spikelet of ear [PO:0006353], lower floret of sessile spikelet of ear [PO:0006351], upper floret of pedicellate spikelet of ear [PO:0006350], upper floret of sessile spikelet of ear [PO:0006352], tassel floret [PO:0006310], lower floret of pedicellate spikelet of tassel [PO:0006313], lower floret of sessile spikelet of tassel [PO:0006315], upper floret of pedicellate spikelet of tassel [PO:0006314], upper floret of sessile spikelet of tassel [PO:0006316]. The development of an androecium in an ear floret of a normal maize plant is aborted and is present in a rudimentary state, while the development of an androecium in a tassel floret leads to a functional androecium.

label: gynoecium
description: A collective phyllome structure [PO:0025023] composed all of the carpels [PO:0009030] in a flower [PO:0009046]. If annotating gene expression to a gynoecium with a single carpel [PO:0009030], the annotation should go on carpel. A gynoecium with two or more carpels may be either syncarpous [carpels fused] or apopcarpous [carpels free] or the carpels may be partially fused. The word pistil is used synonymously with gynoecium for a synocarpous gynoecium, and synonymously with carpel for an apocarpous gynoecium, whether it has one or more carpels. In Zea mays, gynoecia of tassel florets and of the lower florets of ear spikelets usually do not develop fully, and they are present in a rudimentary state. If you are annotating to this structure for Zea mays or other grasses, please also add an annotation to the corresponding floret type. Choose the most specific term possible from: spikelet floret [PO:0009082], ear floret [PO:0006354], lower floret of pedicellate spikelet of ear [PO:0006353], lower floret of sessile spikelet of ear [PO:0006351], upper floret of pedicellate spikelet of ear [PO:0006350], upper floret of sessile spikelet of ear [PO:0006352], tassel floret [PO:0006310], lower floret of pedicellate spikelet of tassel [PO:0006313], lower floret of sessile spikelet of tassel [PO:0006315], upper floret of pedicellate spikelet of tassel [PO:0006314], upper floret of sessile spikelet of tassel [PO:0006316].

label: anther
description: A collective plant organ structure (PO:0025007) that is the pollen-bearing part of a stamen (PO:0009029). Generally consists of four pollen sacs (microsporangia) in two anther thecas. If you are annotating to anther or one of its parts for Zea mays or other grasses, please also add an annotation to the corresponding floret type. Choose the most specific term possible from: spikelet floret (PO:0009082), tassel floret (PO:0006310), lower floret of pedicellate spikelet of tassel (PO:0006313), lower floret of sessile spikelet of tassel (PO:0006315), upper floret of pedicellate spikelet of tassel (PO:0006314), upper floret of sessile spikelet of tassel (PO:0006316)

label: filament
description: A stalk (PO:0025066) that is part of a stamen (PO:0009029).

label: connective
description: The part of the stamen that connects the microsporangia/pollen sacs.

label: anther theca
description: A collective plant organ structure (PO:0025007) that is part of an anther (PO:0009066) and consists of a pair of sporangia (PO:0025094) that dehisce down a common slit.

label: plant ovary
description: A plant structure (PO:0009011) that is the basal portion of a carpel (PO:0009030) or group of fused carpels (gynoecium; PO:0009062) and encloses the plant ovule(s) (PO:0020003).

label: stigma
description: A cardinal organ part (PO:0025001), usually apical, that is part of a carpel (PO:0009030) or group of fused carpels on which the pollen (PO:0025281) germinates.

label: style
description: A cardinal organ part (PO:0025001) which is an elongated part of a carpel (PO:0009030) or gynoecium (PO:0009062) between the plant ovary (PO:0009072) and the stigma (PO:0009073), and through which the pollen tube (GO:0090406) grows.

label: staminode
description: Sterile stamen.

label: pericarp
description: A portion of plant tissue [PO:0009007] that is the outer layer [wall] of a fruit [PO:0009001], and develops from a plant ovary [PO:0009072] or a carpel [PO:0009030] wall.

label: exocarp
description: A portion of plant tissue [PO:0009007] that is the outer layer of a pericarp [PO:0009084].

label: endocarp
description: A portion of plant tissue (PO:0009007) that is the innermost differentiated layer of a pericarp (PO:0009084).

label: mesocarp
description: A portion of plant tissue (PO:0009007) that is the middle layer of a pericarp (PO:0009084).

label: seed coat
description: Used only when not specified more precisely; see testa, tegmen. A portion of plant tissue that is the covering of a seed derived from ovular - mainly integumentary - tissue.

label: endosperm
description: A portion of plant tissue [PO:0009007] which is a maximal portion of nutritive plant tissue in a seed [PO:0009010].

label: plant ovule
description: A plant organ (PO:0009008) that has as parts a nucellus (PO:0020020) in which a female gametophyte (PO:0025279) is located, one or two integuments (PO:0020021), and a funicle (PO:0020006).

label: cotyledon
description: A vascular leaf [PO:0009025] formed at the first shoot node [PO:0005004] of a plant embryo [PO:0009009] or a seedling [PO:0000003].

label: epicotyl
description: The first stem internode [PO:0020142] above the cotyledonary node [PO:0025321] of a plant embryo [PO:0009009] or a seedling [PO:0000003].

label: petiole
description: A stalk (PO:0025066) of a vascular leaf (PO:0009025).

label: leaf lamina
description: A phyllome lamina [PO:0025396] that is the part of a leaf [PO:0025034] exclusive of the petiole [PO:0020038] or leaf sheath [PO:0020104], if either is present. A leaf lamina is usually dorsiventrally flattened, but may be flattened in a median plant [perpendicular to the axis] in the case of phyllodes [PO:0025335] or other ensiform leaves [PO:0025333].

label: leaf base
description: A phyllome base (PO:0025140) that is part of a leaf (PO:0025034).

label: simple leaf
description: A leaf in which the lamina is undivided.

label: compound leaf
description: A leaf having two or more distinct leaflets that are evident as such from early in development.

label: leaflet
description: A cardinal organ part [PO:0025001] that is one of the ultimate segments of a compound leaf [PO:0020043].

label: hypocotyl
description: A stem internode [PO:0020142] below the cotyledonary node [PO:0025321] and transitional to a root [PO:0009005] of a plant embryo [PO:0009009] or a seedling [PO:0000003].

label: stomium
description: A plant anatomical space that is a slit in an anther lobe formed from when a dehiscence zone dehisces.

label: lateral root
description: A root [PO:0009005] that develops from a lateral root primordium [PO:0000016] that is part of another root on the same plant.

label: primary root
description: A root [PO:0009005] that develops directly from an seedling radicle [PO:0020127]. The first root of a plant. In dicots and gymnosperms it becomes the tap root, the central axis of a root system [PO:0025025].

label: leaf margin
description: A phyllome margin [PO:0025018] that is part of a leaf [PO:0025034].

label: leaf apex
description: A phyllome apex (PO:0025139) that is part of a leaf (PO:0025034).

label: leaf lamina vein
description: A phyllome lamina vein [PO:0025348] that is part of a leaf lamina vascular system [PO:0000048].

label: leaf midvein, midrib
description: A primary leaf vein (PO:0025413) that is the central vein of a vascular leaf (PO:0009025).

label: secondary leaf vein
description: A leaf lamina vein [PO:0020138] arising from a primary leaf vein [PO:0025413].

label: stem node
description: A shoot axis node [PO:0005004] that is part of a stem [PO:0009047].

label: whorl, floral whorl
formatted label and identifier: collective phyllome structure, whorl, floral whorl [PO:0025023]
description: A collective plant organ structure [PO:0025007] that consists of two or more phyllomes [PO:0006001] originating from the same node or from one or more adjacent nodes with compressed shoot internodes [PO:0005005].

label: root system
description: A collective plant organ structure [PO:0025007] that produces root meristems [PO:0006085], the plant structures [PO:0009011] that arise from them and the parts thereof. Generally the below ground portion of a vascular plant.

label: leaf
description: A phyllome [PO:0006001] that is not associated with a reproductive structure.

label: lamina
description: A cardinal part of multi-tissue plant structure [PO:0025498] that is thin and flat.

label: branch
description: A shoot axis (PO:00025029) that develops from an axillary bud meristem (PO:0000232) or from equal divisions of a meristematic apical cell (PO:0030007).

label: reproductive shoot system
description: A shoot system [PO:0009006] in the sporophytic phase that has as part at least one sporangium [PO:0025094].

label: plant anatomical space; lumen
description: An anatomical space that is part of a plant. CARO:0000005 'anatomical space' is defined as: An immaterial anatomical entity of three dimensions, that is generated by morphogenetic or other physiologic processes, and is bounded by an anatomical surface.

label: petiole lamina
description: The entire petiole may be laminar, or the petiole may be more or less rounded in cross section with laminar extensions. A lamina [PO:0025060] that is part of a petiole [PO:0020038].

label: portion of plant substance
description: Refers to organism substance [CARO:0000004] which is defined as: Material anatomical entity in a gaseous, liquid, semisolid or solid state; produced by anatomical structures or derived from inhaled and ingested substances that have been modified by anatomical structures as they pass through the body and that does not have inherent 3D shape generated by coordinated expression of the organism's own genome. For plants, the word "body" refers to a whole plant, or part thereof. Includes substances such as latex, xylem sap, phloem sap, resin, mucilage, oil, cuticle, cutin, and sporopollenin. A portion of organism substance that is or was part of a plant.

label: prickle
description: Often found on stems and leaves. A portion of epidermis (PO:0005679) that is a sclerified outgrowth.

label: thorn
description: A branch that is a sclerified, pointed outgrowth. A thorn is a short, pointed (PATO:0002258) woody structure, may be branched.

label: spine leaf
description: A leaf that is a sclerified and pointed and lacks a lamina. See also stipule spine (PO:0025174).

label: spine stipule
description: See also leaf spine (PO:0025173). A stipule that is sclerified and pointed.

label: pollen
description: A microgametophyte (PO:0025280) that develops from a microspore (PO:0020048) is located in a pollen sac (PO:0025277).

label: phyllode
description: An adult ensiform leaf with a lamina that develops in a median plane, rather a transverse plane, throughout the length of the leaf and is a result of increased activity of the adaxial meristem early in development.

label: cladode
description: A shoot axis that is flattened and expanded. Has an increased surface area for photosynthesis and may function similar to leaves in plants that have no or small leaves, such as cacti. Consists of one to several internodes and nodes. Cladodes bear scale leaves (or leaf scars where temporary leaves have fallen off) that subtend axillary buds.

label: intercellular space
description: A plant anatomical space that is part of a portion of plant tissue between two or more cells.

label: epicuticular wax
description: A portion of cuticular wax (PO:0025386) that forms crystalloids or a smooth film on the exterior of a plant cuticle (PO:0000022). Epicuticular waxes may take a variety of forms, such as plates, ribbons, tubes, and rods.

label: plant fiber cell
description: A sclerenchyma cell [PO:0000077] that is elongated and tapering.

label: primary leaf vein
description: Generally the largest and most prominent of the leaf veins. A leaf may have more than one primary vein. The central primary vein is the midvein (PO:0020139). Vein orders only apply to hierarchically branching vein patterns, not to dichotomously branching vein patterns, as found in some ferns and gymnosperms.

label: xylem vessel
description: A portion of xylem [PO:0005352] tissue that has as parts a tube-like series of vessel members [PO:0002003], the common walls of which have perforations.

label: secondary xylem tracheid
description: A tracheid PO:0000301 that is part of a portion of secondary xylem tissue [PO:0005848].

label: whole plant fruit development stage
description: A sporophyte reproductive stage that begins when a fruit [PO:0009001] on a whole plant [PO:0000003] that is not currently participating in a whole plant fruit development stage begins a fruit initiation stage [PO:0025503], and ends with the earliest of the following: [1] the whole plant begins a sporophyte senescent stage [PO:0007017], [2] the whole plant begins a sporophyte dormant stage [PO:0007132], or [3] all fruits on the whole plant are finished ripening.

label: leaf lamina lobes
description: A phyllome lobe [PO:0025514] that is a projection on a leaf lamina margin [PO:0025009] for which the corresponding leaf sinus [PO:0025384] extends one quarter or more of the distance to the center of the long axis of the leaf lamina [PO:0020039]. A leaf lobe may be either rounded or angular at the tip, and may have leaf teeth [PO:0025518] or leaf crenae [PO:0025519] on its margin. The corresponding leaf sinus may be rounded or angular.

label: leaf lamina tooth
description: A phyllome lamina tooth [PO:0025515] that is an angular projection on a leaf margin [PO:0020128] for which the corresponding leaf sinus [PO:0025384] extends less than one quarter of the distance to the center of the long axis of the leaf lamina [PO:0020039].

label: vegetative shoot system
description: A shoot system [PO:0009006] that has as parts only vegetative tissues and organs.

label: spine petiole
description: A petiole (PO:0020038) that is sclerified and persistent. The petiole (PO:0020038) abcisses longitudinally and the leaf lamina (PO:0020039) withers.

label: fruit pedicel
description: A pedicel (PO:0030112) that bears a fruit (PO:0009001).

label: shoot system meristem
description: A portion of meristem tissue (PO:0009013) that is part of a shoot system (PO:0009006).

label: strobilus
description: A reproductive shoot system (PO:0025082) consisting of a number of sporophylls (PO:0009026) or plant ovule (PO:0020003)-bearing modified leaves (PO:0025034) grouped terminally on a stem (PO:0009047).

label: plant embryo cotyledon
description: A cotyledon (PO:0020030) that is part of a plant embryo (PO:0009009).

label: flowering stage
description: A flower development stage (PO:0007615) that begins when pollen (PO:0025281) is released by anther dehiscence (GO:0009901) and/or the stigma (PO:0009073) is receptive and ends with the process of pollination (GO:0009856) and/or floral organ senescence (GO:0080187).

label: heatwood
description: A portion of secondary xylem (PO:0005848) that lacks living secondary xylem parenchyma cells (PO:0004525).

label: plant habit
description: [no definition]

label: model parameter
description: A model parameter is a data item which is part of a model and which is meant to characterize an theoritecal or unknown population. a model parameter may be estimated by considering the properties of samples presumably taken from the theoritecal population

label: reaction rate
description: Reaction rate is a measurement datum which represents the speed of a chemical reaction turning reactive species into product species of event (i.e the number of such conversions)s occuring over a time interval

label: substrate concentration
description: Substrate concentration is a scalar measurement datum which denotes the amount of molecular entity involved in an enzymatic reaction (or catalytic chemical reaction) and whose role in that reaction is as substrate.

label: ordinal variable
description: Ordinal variable is a categorical variable where the discrete possible values are ordered or correspond to an implicit ranking

label: continuous variable
description: A continuous variable is one for which, within the limits the variable ranges, any value is possible.

label: categorical variable
description: A categorical variable is a variable which that can only assume a finite number of value and cast observation in a small number of categories

label: dimensionless ratio
description: A ratio where the numerator and denominator are expressed in the same unit.

label: weighted arithmetic mean
description: The weighted arithmetic mean is a measure of central tendency that is the sum of the products of each observed value and their respective non-negative weights, divided by the sum of the weights, such that the contribution of each observed value to the mean may defer according to its respective weight. It is defined by the formula: A = sum[vi*wi]/sum[wi], where 'i' ranges from 1 to n, 'vi' is the value of each observation, and 'wi' is the value of the respective weight for each observed value. The weighted arithmetic mean is a kind of mean similar to an ordinary arithmetic mean [the most common type of average], except that instead of each of the data points contributing equally to the final average, some data points are weighted, meaning they contribute more than others. The weighted arithmetic mean is often used if one wants to combine average values from samples of the same population with different sample sizes.

label: calcium sensitivity
description: Sensitivity to the calcium content in the growth medium. Plays an important role in cell wall synthesis and enzyme activities.

label: plant morphology trait
description: A plant trait [TO:0000387] which is a morphological quality of a plant anatomical entity [PO:0025131] or a constituent cellular component [GO:0005575] contained therein. Includes traits of plant structures [PO:0009011] such as plant cell [PO:0009002], plant organ [PO:0009008], portion of plant tissue [PO:0009007], vascular system [PO:0000034], whole plant [PO:0000003] and seed [PO:0009010], as well as those of plant anatomical spaces [PO:0025117] and portions of plant substance [PO:0025161].

label: root morphology trait
description: A plant axis morphology trait [TO:0000738] which is a quality of a root [PO:0025025].

label: plant embryo morphology trait
description: A whole plant morphology trait [TO:0000398] which is a quality of a plant embryo [PO:0009009].

label: root dry weight, root dry mass
formatted label and identifier: root dry weight, root dry mass [TO:0000078]
description: The average dry weight of the root determined in a study.

label: root mass density
description: Determined as the dry mass of roots per unit soil volume at a given soil section.

label: leaf water potential
description: Water potential of a leaf.

label: leaf length
description: Actual measurements, in centimeters of the leaf. Refers to length [PATO:0000122]: A 1-D extent quality which is equal to the distance between two points.

label: leaf relative water content
description: Leaf relative water content is determined at midday (12.00 noon).

label: stress trait
description: Response by the plant in terms of resistivity or sensitivity to either the biotic or the abiotic types of stress.

label: seed weight, seed mass
description: A seed morphology trait [TO:0000184] which is the weight of a seed [PO:0009010].

label: seed morphology trait
description: A multi-tissue plant structure morphology trait [TO:0000836] which is a quality of a seed [PO:0009010].

label: germination ratio
description: Ratio of germinated to non-germinated seeds.

label: leaf angle
description: A leaf attitude [TO:0000206] which is the angle of a leaf [PO:0025034] measured against the stem.

label: plant height
description: A whole plant morphology trait [TO:0000398] which is the height of a whole plant [PO:0000003]. Comment: Refers to: height [PATO_0000119]: A 1-D extent quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's vertical dimension of extension.

label: water stress trait
description: Response by the plant in terms of sensitivity to water stress (quality and quantity of water).

label: growth media pH sensitivity
description: A growth media composition sensitivity [TO:0000238] which is the response of the plant to the pH of the growth media [soil/culture media], whether it be acidic or alkaline.

label: leaf thickness
description: A leaf morphology trait [TO:0000748] which is the thickness of a leaf [PO:0025034].

label: perianth morphology trait
description: A collective phyllome structure morphology trait [TO:0000845] which is a quality of a perianth [PO:0009058]

label: drought tolerance
description: Becoming tolerant to drought like conditions of minimal or no water content in the growth environment.. Often the plants exhibiting high salt tolerance also exhibit drought tolerance.

label: biochemical trait
description: A plant trait [TO:0000387] which is a quality of a chemical entity [CHEBI:24431], a plant metabolite [CHEBI:76924], or a molecular function [GO:0003674], which occurs in a cellular component [GO:0005575], plant anatomical entity [PO:0025131] or during a plant structure development stage [PO:0009012].

label: root to shoot ratio [LENGTH ratio, not mass ratio]
formatted label and identifier: root to shoot ratio [LENGTH ratio, not mass ratio] [TO:0000278]
description: The ratio determined from the parameters evaluated for root length and the shoot length in a study.

label: root mass
description: Root weight may be measured as the average dry or fresh weight of roots. A root morphology trait [TO:0000043] which is the weight of a root [PO:0009005].

label: metabolite content trait
description: The trait associated with an assay to determine the affected metabolite's profile.

label: biological process trait, physiological process trait
formatted label and identifier: biological process trait, physiological process trait [TO:0000283]
description: Refers to process quality [PATO:0001236]: A quality which inheres in an process. A plant trait [TO:0000387] which is a process quality [PATO:0001236] of a biological process [GO:0008150] which occurs in a plant anatomical entity [PO:0025131], a cellular component [GO:0005575], or during a plant structure development stage [PO:0009012].

label: carbohydrate content
description: A metabolite content trait [TO:0000281] which is the amount of carbohydrate [CHEBI:16646] in a plant structure [PO:0009011].

label: soluble protein content
description: Amount of the soluble protein present in the plant or the plant part.

label: total soluble sugar content
description: Total amount of soluble sugar present in the plant or plant part.

label: seed viability
description: [no definition]

label: plant dry weight, plant dry mass
formatted label and identifier: plant dry weight, plant dry mass [TO:0000352]
description: The dry weight of the whole plant.

label: plant growth and development trait
description: A plant trait (TO:0000387) which is the growth (GO:0048590) and development (GO:0032502) of a plant anatomical entity (PO:0025131) or a constituent cellular component (GO:0005575).

label: stem morphology trait
description: A shoot axis morphology trait [TO:0000739] which is the quality of a stem [PO:0009047].

label: leaf width
description: A leaf morphology trait [TO:0000748] which is the width of a leaf [PO:0025034]. Actual measurements, in centimeters of the widest portion of the leaf.

label: plant trait
description: A measurable or observable characteristic of a cellular component [GO:0005575], biological process [GO:0008150] or molecular function [GO:0003674] that is part of, or has participant a plant anatomical entity [PO:0025131] and/or a plant structure development stage [PO:0009012]. This includes physiological, molecular and biochemical traits as well.

label: whole plant morphology trait
description: A plant structure morphology trait [TO:0000839] which is a quality of a whole plant [PO:0000003].

label: seed longevity
description: [no definition]

label: mineral and ion content trait
description: May be measured in a dry mass or in a fresh tissue. A biochemical trait [TO:0000277] that is the amount of a particular mineral or ion constituent occurring in a plant anatomical entity [PO:0025131].

label: vascular tissue morphology trait
description: A portion of plant tissue morphology trait [TO:0000843] which is a quality of a vascular tissue and its parts.

label: chemical stress sensitivity
description: Response by the plant in terms of resistivity or senility to chemical stress.

label: seed shape
description: A seed morphology trait (TO:0000184) which is the shape of a seed (PO:0009010). Seed shape can be a component of seed quality (TO:0000162). Refers to shape (PATO:0000052): A morphological quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's ratios of distances between its features (points, edges, surfaces and also holes etc).

label: leaf shape
description: A leaf morphology trait [TO:0000748] which is the variation in shapes and forms of a leaf [PO:0025034]. Refer to shape [PATO:0000052]: A morphological quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's ratios of distances between its features [points, edges, surfaces and also holes etc].

label: pigment content trait
description: [no definition]

label: carotenoid content
description: The carotenoid content in a plant or plant part. Includes naturally occurring tetra terpenes that are synthesized only in plants.

label: leaf weight, leaf mass
description: A leaf morphology trait [TO:0000505] which is the weight of a leaf [PO:0025034].

label: osmotic adjustment capacity
description: The ability of the plant to adust the osmotic potential under stress conditions.

label: abaxial stomatal frequency
description: Number of stomata present on the abaxial surface of leaf.

label: adaxial stomatal frequency
description: Number of stomata present on the adaxial surface of leaf.

label: leaf area trait
description: Refer to area [PATO:0001323]: A 2-D extent quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's two dimensional extent.

label: leaf position trait
description: A leaf morphology trait (TO:0000748) which is the position of the leaf (PO:0025034) on the plant. Refers to: position (PATO_0000140): A spatial quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's spatial location relative to other objects in the vicinity. Usually measured from the ground. If you are annotating to this term, please add an additional annotation to vascular leaf morphology (TO:0000419) or non-vascular leaf morphology trait (TO:0000925), depending on the species.

label: shoot dry mass
description: The dry weight of the shoot without inflorescence.

label: specific leaf area
description: A leaf area trait [TO:0000540] that is the ratio of the leaf area [TO:0000540] to the leaf dry weight [TO:0001014] or leaf dry mass [TO:New].

label: leaf stomatal complex frequency
description: A vascular leaf morphology trait [TO:0000419] which is the number of leaf stomatal complexes [PO:0025183] present on the leaf surface.

label: shoot fresh mass
description: Fresh weight of the shoot without inflorescence.

label: root fresh mass
description: The average fresh weight of the root determined in a study.

label: protein content
description: The total protein content measured in a plant or a plant part.

label: starch content
description: Amount of starch present in the plant or plant part.

label: turgor pressure
description: The pressure within the cell resulting from the absorption of water into the vacuole and the imbibition of water by the protoplasm.

label: leaf morphology trait
description: A phyllome morphology trait [TO:0000747] which is quality of a leaf [PO:0025034].

label: seedling hypocotyl morphology trait
description: A hypocotyl morphology trait [TO:0000757] which a seedling hypocotyl [PO:0025291].

label: reproductive shoot system morphology trait
description: A shoot system morphology trait [TO:0000077] that is a quality of a reproductive shoot system [PO:0025082].

label: leaf vein morphology trait
description: A vascular leaf morphology trait [TO:0000419] which is a quality of a leaf lamina vein [PO:0020138].

label: leaf attitude
description: Leaf attitude traits refer to the way a leaf is naturally held on the plant. If you are annotating to this term, please add an additional annotation to vascular leaf morphology (TO:0000419) or non-vascular leaf morphology trait (TO:0000925), depending on the species. A leaf morphology trait (TO:0000748) which is the attitude of a leaf (PO:0025034).

label: plant structure morphology trait
description: A plant morphology trait [TO:0000017] which is a quality of a plant structure [PO:0009011].

label: portion of plant tissue morphology trait
formatted label and identifier: portion of plant tissue morphology trait [TO:0000843]
description: A plant structure morphology trait [TO:0000839] which is a quality of a portion of plant tissue [PO:0009007].

label: floral organ morphology trait
description: A plant organ morphology trait [TO:0000736] which is a quality of a floral organ [PO:0025395].

label: tepal morphology trait
description: A phyllome morphology trait [TO:0000747] which is a quality of a tepal [PO:0009033].

label: stem shape trait
description: A stem morphology trait [TO:0000361] which is the shape of a stem [PO:0009047]. Refer to shape [PATO:0000052]: A morphological quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's ratios of distances between its features [points, edges, surfaces and also holes etc].

label: plant phenological trait
description: A growth and development trait [TO:0000357] which is the timing of the occurrence of plant structure development stages [PO:0009012] and the relevant biological processes [GO:0008150].

label: stem mass
description: A stem morphology trait [TO:0000361] which is the weight of a stem [PO:0009047].

label: stem number
description: A shoot system morphology trait [TO:0000077] which is the number of stems [PO:0009047].

label: plant embryo cotyledon color
description: A plant embryo cotyledon morphology trait [TO:0000775] which is the color of the plant embryo cotyledon [PO:0025470].

label: androecium morphology trait
description: A collective phyllome structure morphology trait [TO:0000845] that is a quality of the androecium [PO:0009061].

label: leaf dry weight, leaf dry mass
formatted label and identifier: leaf dry weight, leaf dry mass [TO:0001014]
description: A leaf weight trait [TO:0000505] which is the dry weight of a leaf [PO:0025034].

label: photosynthetic rate
description: The total amount of carbon fixed by the plant per unit time and is measured by determining the changes in CO2 concentration over a plant leaf in a glass enclosure.

label: water use efficiency
description: As determined by the ratio of photosynthetic rate to transpiration rate.

label: osmotic adjustment break point
description: Break point of leaf water potential in the regression of leaf water potential against leaf relative water content.

label: root system depth
description: A root system morphology trait [TO:0000985] which is the depth of the root system [PO:0025025].

label: flowering time trait
description: Often influenced by the environment that includes, day light, temperature and geographic location. A plant phenological trait [TO:0000933] which is a quality of the timing of anthesis [flowering stage; PO:0007616].

label: fruit color
description: A fruit morphology trait [TO:0002617] which is the color of a fruit [PO:0009001]. Refer to color PATO:0000014: A composite chromatic quality composed of hue, saturation and intensity parts.

label: fruit morphology trait
description: A multi-tissue plant structure morphology trait [TO:0000836] which is a quality of a fruit [PO:0009001].

label: leaf margin morphology trait
description: A phyllome margin morphology trait [TO:0000834] which is a quality of a leaf margin [PO:0020128]. Often associated with leaf margin curvature.

label: leaf size trait
description: Refer to size [PATO:0000117]: A morphology quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's physical magnitude.

label: seed maturation
description: This trait can be derived based on the parameters like, degree of grain filling, grain hardness, hull color, grain moisture, etc. It can be determined for (a)synchronously with any of these parameters.

label: plant cell morphology trait
description: A plant cell morphology trait [TO:0002683] which is the size of a plant cell [PO:0009002] type.

label: plant cell size
description: Refer to size [PATO:0000117]: A morphology quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's physical magnitude. A plant cell morphology trait [TO:0002683] which is the size of a plant cell [PO:0009002] type.

label: leaf pubescence
description: A leaf morphology trait (TO:0000748) which is the extent of pubescence (presence of hairs) on the leaf (PO:0025034). Refer to pubescent hair (PATO:0001320): A pilosity quality of being covered with short hairs or soft down.

label: stem fresh mass
description: A stem weight trait [TO:0000952] which is the fresh weight of a stem [PO:0009047].

label: stem dry weight, stem dry mass
formatted label and identifier: stem dry weight, stem dry mass [TO:0003001]
description: A stem mass trait [TO:0000952] which is the dry weight of a stem [PO:0009047].

label: salt tolerance
description: Tolerance to the high salt content in the growth medium.

label: phyllotaxy
description: A leaf morphology trait (TO:0000748) which is the arrangement of the leaves on the shoot of a plant.

label: petal number
description: A petal morphology trait [TO:0000863] which is the number of petals [PO:0009032] in a flower [PO:0009049].

label: plant width
description: The average width of a plant measured across an axis such as the main stem/stalk.

label: leaf trichome density
description: Measurement of trichomes found in per unit area of a leaf.

label: seed texture
description: A seed morphology trait (TO:0000184) which is the texture of a seed (PO:0009010).

label: apical axillary primary branch number
description: [no definition]

label: phenolic compound content
description: Amount of phenolics present in the plant part, whole plant or product.

label: secondary xylem volumetric density, wood volumetric density
formatted label and identifier: secondary xylem volumetric density, wood volumetric density [TO:1000002]
description: A trait which is associated with the volumetric density of a secondary xylem.

label: flower morphology trait
description: A reproductive shoot system morphology trait (TO:0000786) which is a quality of a flower (PO:0009046).

label: shoot system morphology trait
description: A collective plant organ structure morphology trait (TO:0000842) which is a quality of a shoot system (PO:0009006).

label: plant embryo cotyledon morphology trait
description: A cotyledon morphology trait (TO:0000749) which is a quality of a plant embryo cotyledon (PO:0025470).

label: root system morphology trait
description: A collective plant organ structure morphology trait (TO:0000842) which is a quality of a root system (PO:0025025).

label: quantum yield
description: [no definition]

label: life cycle habit
description: Determined for type of life cycle being annual, biannual, perennial etc.

label: root nitrogen content
description: A nitrogen content trait (TO:0020093) which is the amount of nitrogen (CHEBI:51143) in a root (PO:0009005).

label: root system phosphorus content
description: A phosphorus content trait TO:0001024 which is the phosphorus cation (CHEBI:33467) composition in a root system (PO:0025025).

label: seed phosphorus content
description: Amount of phosphorus in the seed.

label: stem phosphorus content
description: A phosphorus content trait (TO:0001024) which is the amount of phosphorus cation (CHEBI:33467) in a stem (PO:0009047).

label: leaf carbon content
description: A carbon content trait (TO:0000466) which is the amount of carbon (CHEBI:27594) in a leaf (PO:0025034).

label: xylem sap
description: A plant sap (PO:0025538) that is an aqueous solution which may contain mineral elements, nutrients, and plant hormones, and is transported from the root system (PO:0025025) toward the leaves through the tracheary elements (PO:0000290) of the xylem.

label: cell layer
description: Portion of tissue, that consists of single layer of cells connected to each other by cell junctions.

label: reproductive structure
description: Any anatomical structure that is part of the reproductive system.

label: adult (adult organism)
description: A multicellular organism that existence_ends_with a post-juvenile adult stage and existence_starts_with a post-juvenile adult stage.

label: time unit
description: A unit which is a standard measure of the dimension in which events occur in sequence.

label: month
description: A time unit which is approximately equal to the length of time of one of cycle of the moon's phases which in science is taken to be equal to 30 days.

label: degree
description: A plane angle unit which is equal to 1/360 of a full rotation or 1.7453310^[-2] rad.

label: experimental condition
description: A state of being, an external or environmental factor or a treatment observed or administered prior to or concurrent with an investigative procedure such as an assessment of a morphological or physiological state or property in a single individual or sample or in a group of individuals or samples, especially a state, factor or treatment which has the potential to influence the outcome of such an assessment.

label: community
description: In ecology, a community is an assemblage of two or more populations of different species occupying the same geographical area. (wikipedia) An ecological unit composed of a group of organisms or a population of different species occupying a particular area, usually interacting with each other and their environment.

label: tree diameter at breast height
description: Domain protocol for measuring the diameter of a tree. Measured at a specified, average distance from the ground, eg 4.5 ft [or average person's breast height]. May be measured as circumference, then divided by pi.

label: mass fraction
description: Ratio of the mass of a substance to the total mass of a mixture. With a denominator of 100, mass fraction can also be expressed as percentage by mass

label: mass fraction of carbon dioxide
description: Ratio of the mass of carbon dioxide to the total mass of a mixture.

label: d13C
description: Note that this measurement uses the lowercase Greek letter delta [δ]. A stable carbon isotope ratio, which is a measure of the ratio of stable isotopes 13C and 12C.

label: carbon stable isotope ratio
description: An isotopic signature is a ratio of non-radiogenic 'stable isotopes', stable radiogenic isotopes, or unstable radioactive isotopes of particular elements in an investigated material. The ratios of isotopes in a sample material are measured by isotope ratio mass spectrometry. The atomic mass of different isotopes affect their chemical kinetic behavior, leading to natural isotope separation processes. For example, different sources and sinks of methane have different affinity for the 12C and 13C isotopes, which allows distinguishing between different sources by the 13C/12C ratio in methane in the air.

label: count density
description: Number density is an intensive quantity used to describe the degree of concentration of countable objects in a given physical space.

label: d18O in water
description: [no definition]

label: d18O
description: A stable oxygen isotope ratio which is the ratio of oxygen 18 and oxygen 16. Note that this measurement uses the lower case Greek letter delta [δ].

label: count per unit length
description: A ratio [PATO:0001470], which is a count [NCIT:C25463] per unit length [EnvThes:22004].

label: accessory cost
description: Biomass investment [OMIT:0008566] in reproductive tissues [CARO:0000043] other than the seeds [PO:0009010]. These tissues include prepollination (flower, nectar, and pollen) and postpollination (packaging, protective and dispersal [EnvThes:21038] tissues) as well as aborted floral parts.

label: ambient photosynthetic rate
description: Photosynthetic rate [TO:0001015] in a plant whose photosystem [GO:0009521] I and II reaction centers [GO:0009538; GO:0009539] are exposed to ambient [NCIT:C62306] photosynthetically active radiation [ENVO:01001864] levels and ambient atmospheric carbon dioxide [ENVO:01000451] concentrations [PATO:0000033] while the measurement is made.

label: bark dry mass
description: A bark mass trait [APD:xxxxxxx] which is the dry [PATO:0001824] mass [PATO:0000125] of a section of bark [PO:0004518].

label: bark mass trait
description: A bark morphology trait [APD:xxxxxxx] which is the mass [PATO:0000125] of a section of bark [PO:0004518].

label: bark morphology trait
description: A plant structure morphology trait [TO:0000736] which is a quality of bark [PO:0004518].

label: bark water content
description: A bark mass trait [APD:xxxxxxx] which is the mass [PATO:0000125] of water [CHEBI:15377] in a section of bark [PO:0004518].

label: biomass allocation trait
description: A plant morphology trait [TO:0000017] pertaining to the investment [OMIT:0008566] of biomass [ENVO:01000155] into a specific tissue [UBERON:0000479] or tissues as a proportion [PATO:0001470] of an organism's [OBI:0100026] total [NCIT:C25304] biomass.

label: calcicole
description: A plant that grows best in calcareous soil.

label: calcifuge
description: A plant that grows poorly in calcareous soil.

label: carbon dioxide concentration trait
description: A plant gas exchange trait which is the concentration [PATO:0000033] of carbon dioxide [CHEBI:16526].

label: cell or tissue mineral and ion content trait
formatted label and identifier: cell or tissue mineral and ion content trait [APD:40024]
description: A mineral and ion content trait [TO:0000465] which is the mineral or ion content of specific cells [CL:0000000] or tissues [UBERON:0000479].

label: coarse root
description: A root greater than 2 mm in diameter. The alternative to fine roots [EnvThes:20581].

label: delta notation
description: Notation that expresses the variation of an isotopic ratio of an element, relative to the isotopic ratio of a standard

label: diaspore
description: A plant's dispersal unit, which can be a seed, an entire fruit, or a seed with some additional tissue that aids its dispersal.

label: environmental tolerance trait
description: A plant life history trait [APD:xxxxxxx] indicating adaptations [NCIT:C158868] to specific environmental conditions [ENVO:01000203] or tolerance [NCIT:C43414] to specific environmental stresses [EnvThes:21245].

label: fire response trait
description: A plant life history trait [APD:xxxxxxx] indicating adaptations [NCIT:C158868] to increase survival rate [EnvThes:21065] or seed germination [GO_0009845] rate following fire [ENVO:01000786] or indicating a plant's response [NCIT:C25755] to fire.

label: gas exchange trait
description: A plant photosynthesis trait [APD:xxxxxxx] pertaining to the movement [NCIT:C37994] of carbon dioxide [CHEBI:16526], water [CHEBI:15377], and oxygen [CHEBI:15379] into and out of a plant cellular metabolic processes [GO:0044237] where these molecules are the reactant [SIO:000879] or product [SIO:010363].

label: genetic structures trait
description: A plant life history trait [APD:xxxxxxx] pertaining to genetic structures [OMIT:0022986].

label: ignition
description: The act of causing something to start burning [Merriam-Webster Dictionary]

label: interspecific interactions trait
description: A plant life history trait [APD:xxxxxxx] that captures an interspecific interaction between organisms [GO:0044419].

label: fresh mass
description: The mass [PATO:0000125] of tissue [CARO_0000043] before it is dried; the mass of the tissue when it is fresh [EnvThes:21976].

label: leaf optical properties trait
description: Leaf morphology trait [APD:xxxxxxx] associated with the leaf's optical [NCIT:C16940] properties, including the absorption [soprocw:Absorption], transmission [soprocw:Transmission], and reflection [soprocw:Reflection] of light [OMIT:0009112].

label: leaf stomatal complex morphology trait
description: A vascular leaf morphology trait [TO:0000419] which is a quality of the stomatal complexes [PO:0002000] present on the leaf surface.

label: leaf water content
description: A leaf mass trait [TO:0000505] which is the total mass [PATO:0000125] of water [CHEBI:15377] in a leaf [PO:0025034].

label: life history trait
description: A plant trait [TO:0000387] pertaining to an individual's life history [ECOCORE:00000018].

label: lipid content trait
description: A metabolite content trait [TO:0000281] which is the amount of lipid [CHEBI:18059] in a plant structure [PO:0009011].

label: mass per area ratio
description: The ratio [PATO:0001470] of the mass [PATO:0000125] of one constituent to the area [PATO:0001323] of a second constituent.

label: maximum photosynthetic rate, Amax
description: Photosynthetic rate [TO:0001015] in a plant whose photosystem [GO:0009521] I and II reaction centers [GO:0009538; GO:0009539] are saturated [NCIT_C61427] by photosynthetically active radiation [ENVO:01001864] and which is exposed to saturating atmospheric carbon dioxide [ENVO:01000451] concentrations [PATO:0000033] while the measurement is made..

label: merism
description: The repetition of similar parts, units, or segments within the structure of an organism. [www.lexico.com]

label: non-structural carbohydrates
description: Carbohydrates [CHEBI:16646], including starches [CHEBI:28017] and sugars [APD:xxxxxxx], that are relatively easy to metabolise [NCIT:C19536] by both plants and animals.

label: nutrient recycling trait
description: A plant physiological process traits [TO:0000283] associated with the resorption [NCIT:C93204] and recycling [NCIT:C126395] of macronutrients [CHEBI:33937] and micronutrients [CHEBI:27027] as plant structures [PO:0009011] senesce [PATO:0001487].

label: pendulous
description: Hanging downward loosely or freely. [Simpson]

label: per unit mass
description: A ratio [PATO:0001470], where the denominator [NCIT:C80489] is a measure of mass [PATO:0000125].

label: photosynthesis trait
description: A plant physiological process traits [TO:0000283] associated with photosynthesis [GO:0015979].

label: photosystem performance trait
description: A plant photosynthesis trait [APD:xxxxxxx] pertaining to the performance [NCIT:C60778] of the photosystem [GO:0009521] complexes, especially with regard to how effectively they process photosynthetically active radiation [ENVO:01001864] during the photosynthesis light reactions [GO:0019684].

label: placentation
description: Referring to the position [PATO:0000140] of the ovules [PO:0020003] within the ovary [PO:0009072]. [Plant Systematics]

label: whole plant leaf dry mass
description: A leaf mass trait [TO:0000505] which is the sum of the leaf dry mass [TO:0000505] of all leaves [PO:0025034] of a whole plant [PO:0000003] [from TOP].

label: plant phenological life history trait
description: A plant life history trait [APD:xxxxxxx] which is a plant phenological trait [TO:0000933].

label: whole plant stem dry mass
description: A stem mass trait [TO:0000952] which is the sum of the stem dry mass [TO:0003001] of all leaves [PO:0009047] of a whole plant [PO:0000003] [dervied from TOP].

label: whole plant dry mass
description: The dry mass [PATO:0000125] of a whole plant [PO:0000003].

label: plant structure strength trait
description: A plant structure morphology trait [TO:0000736] pertaining to the strength [PATO:0001230] of a plant structure [PO:0009011] and often indicating the amount of work [PATO:0001026] required to break or deform the plant structure.

label: pollinator
description: A pollinator is an animal that intentionally or unintentionally moves pollen from the male anther of a flower to the female stigma of a flower. [Wikipedia]

label: punch
description: The force [PATO:0001035] required to punch a hole.

label: root branchiness trait
description: A root system morphology trait [TO:0000985] which is the branchiness [PATO:0002009] of the root system [PO:0025025].

label: saturated photosynthetic rate, Asat
description: Photosynthetic rate [TO:0001015] in a plant whose photosystem [GO:0009521] I and II reaction centers [GO:0009538; GO:0009539] are saturated [NCIT_C61427] by photosynthetically active radiation [ENVO:01001864] and which is exposed to ambient [NCIT:C62306] atmospheric carbon dioxide [ENVO:01000451] concentrations [PATO:0000033] while the measurement is made.

label: smoulder combustion
description: The slow, flameless form of combustion, sustained by the heat evolved when oxygen directly attacks the surface of a condensed-phase fuel. [Wikipedia]

label: spiral [APT]
description: A spatial pattern where discrete entities are arranged in a coil [PATO:0000404].

label: stable isotope ratio determination
description: A mineral and ion content trait [TO:0000465] which is a ratio [PATO:0001470] of two naturally occurring stable isotopes [EnvThes:20310], generally expressed in delta notation.

label: stem fresh mass
description: A stem mass trait [TO:0000952] which is the mass [PATO:0000125] of a fresh [EnvThes:21976] stem [PO:0009047], indicating its mass before it is dried.

label: stem water content
description: A stem mass trait [TO:0000952] which is the total mass [PATO:0000125] of water [CHEBI:15377] in a stem [PO:0009047].

label: structural carbohydrates
description: Long-chain carbohydrates [CHEBI:16646] [ploysaccharides [CHEBI:18154]], including cellulose [CHEBI:62967] and hemicellulose [CHEBI:61266], that comprise cell walls [GO:0009505] and other plant structural components.

label: sugar
description: An informal grouping of carbohydrates [CHEBI:16646] that includes monosaccharides [CHEBI:35381] and disaccharides [CHEBI:36233].

label: total plant reproductive tissue dry mass
formatted label and identifier: total plant reproductive tissue dry mass [APD:40108]
description: A reproductive shoot system morphology trait [TO:0000786] which is the total dry mass of flower buds [PO:0000056], flowers [PO:0009046], fruits [PO:0009001], and seeds [PO:0009010] produced by the plant.

label: total plant seed dry mass
description: A seed mass trait [TO:0000181] which is the total mass [PATO:0000125] of seeds [PO:0009010] produced by the plant.

label: vessel lumen
description: The lumen [PO:0025117] of the xylem vessel [PO:0025417].

label: vestiture
description: Trichome cover [TO:0006066], a combination of trichome type [TO:0000911], length [PATO:0000122], strength [PATO:0001230], shape [PATO:0000052], density [PATO:0001019], and color [PATO:0000014] [Simpson glossary]

label: water saturated leaf
description: A leaf morphology trait [TO:0000505] which is a leaf

label: water transport trait, hydraulic trait
description: A plant physiological process trait [TO:0000283] pertaining to the movement [NCIT:C37994] of water [CHEBI:15377] through a plant's vascular system [PO:0000034], including water stress traits [TO:0000237].

label: whole plant phenotype trait
description: A plant life history trait [APD:xxxxxxx] which is a whole plant phenotype [FLOPO:0000089].

label: xylem vessel morphology trait
description: A vascular tissue morphology trait [TO:0000470] which is a quality of a xylem vessel [PO:0025417].

label: pressure-volume curve
description: A plot of the relationship between tissue water content and tissue water potential, which is used in plant water-relations studies to understand tissue/cell elasticity, cell turgor, and cell osmotic potential.
